rough%20its%20narrative%2C%20changed%20culture%20and%2For%20shaped%20culture%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BSomewhere%20along%20the%20way%2C%20we%20lost%20the%20art%20of%20that%20brand-merchant%20storytelling%20and%20became%20a%20retailer%20that%20sold%20stuff.%20So%20we%20had%20to%20go%20in%20and%20edit.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20what%20Dickson%20said%20about%20what%20the%20retailer%20and%20its%20subsidiary%20brands%20got%20wrong%20in%20the%20past%20%E2%80%94%20and%20how%20he's%20%26quot%3Breinvigorating%26quot%3B%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223750%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Richard%20Dickson%2C%20CEO%20of%20Gap%20Inc.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68548d403d5881a51c1bbf5f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222842%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERichard%20Dickson%2C%20CEO%20of%20Gap%20Inc.%3Cp%3EJohn%20Nacion%2FVariety%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EDickson%20joined%20as%20CEO%20in%202023%2C%20after%20more%20than%2020%20years%20at%20another%20iconic%20brand%2C%20toymaker%20Mattel.%20There%2C%20as%20BI%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgap-company-history-rise-and-fall-pictures-2019-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Epreviously%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20he%20was%20credited%20with%20reviving%20the%20Barbie%20franchise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20came%20on%20as%20Gap%20had%20been%20facing%20years%20of%20underperformance%20and%20brand%20identity%20issues%20as%20other%20fast%20fashion%20retailers%20gained%20steam.%20But%20the%20appeal%20he%20saw%20when%20joining%20as%20CEO%20nearly%20two%20years%20ago%2C%20he%20said%2C%20was%20that%20%26quot%3Beverybody%20wants%20Gap%20to%20win.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20not%20haters%20out%20there%20of%20Gap.%20There's%2C%20to%20some%20extent%2C%20what%20happened%3F%20Where%20did%20it%20go%3F%20I%20used%20to%2C%20if%20you%20will%2C%20shop%20at%20Gap%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThese%20are%20fertile%20ground%20ingredients%20for%20any%20marketing%2Fbusiness%20narrative.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGap%20has%20been%20around%20for%20more%20than%2050%20years%2C%20and%20had%20its%20heyday%20in%20late%2090s%20with%20iconic%20commercials%20like%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DXJ735krOiPo%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EKhaki%20Swing%3C%2Fa%3E%20video%2C%20which%20he%20cited%20in%20the%20conversation%20with%20the%20Journal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20brand%20started%20and%20sort%20of%20personified%20itself%20by%20celebrating%20big%20product%20ideas%20into%20major%20campaigns%20that%20were%20about%20what%20we'll%20call%20fashion-tainment%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20the%20company%20is%20getting%20back%20to%20that.%20Recent%20examples%20include%20pop%20singer%20Troye%20Sivan's%20baggy%20jeans%20campaign%20with%20Gap%2C%20plus%20Banana%20Republic's%20recent%20partnership%20with%20actor%20Patrick%20Schwarzenegger%2C%20who%20gained%20popularity%20in%20the%20hit%20TV%20show%20%26quot%3BThe%20White%20Lotus.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20even%20though%20the%20brand%20is%20attempting%20to%20transform%2C%20it%20won't%20be%20spending%20more%20on%20marketing%2C%20said%20Dickson%20%E2%80%94%20the%20focus%20will%20be%20more%20on%20what%20they%20spend%20on%20and%20how%20those%20strategies%20come%20across%20to%20consumers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BToday%2C%20you%20don't%20need%20to%20spend%20more%2C%20you%20need%20to%20be%20more%20effective%20in%20the%20stories%20that%20you're%20trying%20to%20tell.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20he%20joined%20in%202023%2C%20he's%20also%20been%20trying%20to%20dial%20back%20Gap's%20infamous%20and%20constant%20%26quot%3Bpercentage%20off%26quot%3B%20promos.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20had%20gone%20into%20a%20Gap%20store%20a%20year%20ago%2C%20or%20Old%20Navy%2C%20you%20were%20to%20some%20extent%20bombarded%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%2