The%20explosion%20is%20the%20fourth%20failure%20for%20SpaceX's%20Starship%20rockets%20this%20year.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESpaceX%20uses%20failures%20to%20improve%20%E2%80%94%20but%20it's%20supposed%20to%20put%20astronauts%20on%20the%20moon%20by%202027.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ESpaceX's%20flagship%20rockets%20keep%20blowing%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Wednesday%20night%2C%20one%20of%20the%20Elon%20Musk-run%20space%20technology%20company's%20latest%20rockets%20erupted%20into%20an%20inferno%20on%20the%20launchpad.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20explosion%2C%20which%20enveloped%20a%20portion%20of%20SpaceX's%20Starbase%20campus%20in%20Texas%20in%20fire%20and%20smoke%2C%20was%20meant%20to%20be%20a%20routine%20test%20ahead%20of%20a%20launch%20for%20the%20company's%20Starship%20program.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20plans%20to%20use%20Starship%20rockets%20%E2%80%94%20the%20successor%20to%20its%20Falcon%20models%20%E2%80%94%20to%20conduct%20missions%20to%20the%20moon%2C%20and%20eventually%2C%20Mars.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWednesday's%20explosion%20marks%20the%20fourth%20consecutive%20failure%20for%20SpaceX's%20Starship%20rockets%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20May%2C%20a%20Starship%20rocket%20successfully%20made%20it%20through%20the%20Earth's%20atmosphere%20%E2%80%94%20but%20failed%20to%20release%20a%20payload%20of%20practice%20satellites%20into%20space%20and%20then%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fspacex-starship-flight-nine-launch-satellite-first-payload-reentry-test-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Espun%20out%20of%20control%20on%20its%20trip%20back%20to%20the%20planet%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Starship%20rockets%20also%20exploded%20on%20two%20other%20trips%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpaceX%20has%20embraced%20its%20failures%2C%20using%20data%20collected%20from%20explosions%20and%20missteps%20to%20improve%20future%20products.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWednesday's%20explosion%20was%20intended%20to%20be%20a%20%26quot%3Bstatic%20fire%20test%2C%26quot%3B%20where%20the%20engines%20fire%20while%20the%20rocket%20is%20held%20on%20the%20launchpad%20with%20clamps%2C%20rather%20than%20launched%20into%20the%20atmosphere.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMusk%20brushed%20off%20the%20mishap%20as%20%26quot%3Bjust%20a%20scratch.%26quot%3B%20He%20said%20that%20preliminary%20data%20showed%20the%20failure%20was%20related%20to%20a%20container%20of%20pressurized%20nitrogen%20in%20the%20payload%20bay.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20further%20investigation%20confirms%20that%20this%20is%20what%20happened%2C%20it%20is%20the%20first%20time%20ever%20for%20this%20design%2C%26quot%3B%20Musk%20wrote%20on%20X%2C%20formerly%20Twitter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20representative%20for%20SpaceX%20didn't%20immediately%20respond%20to%20Business%20Insider's%20request%20for%20comment.%20On%20X%2C%20the%20company%20said%20the%20test%20experienced%20%26quot%3Ba%20major%20anomaly.%26quot%3B%20It%20said%20all%20of%20the%20company's%20personnel%20were%20safe%20and%20accounted%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20year's%20string%20of%20failures%20marks%20a%20stark%20departure%20from%20last%20year%2C%20where%20the%20Starship%20program%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fspacex-starship-flight-four-ocean-splashdown-elon-musk-plans-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebetter%20success%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20proving%20that%20its%20rockets%20could%20be%20reused%20and%20even%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-spacex-starship-landing-super-heavy-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eland%20vertically%20after%20a%20trip%20to%20space%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20SpaceX%20is%20a%20private%20company%2C%20Musk%20had%20come%20under%20scrutiny%20from%20Tesla%20shareholders%20earlier%20this%20year%20over%20his%20role%20in%20President%20Donald%20Trump's%20administration.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20number%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-stock-elon-musk-doge-tsla-investor-letter-ceo-succession-2025-05%5C%22%20target%3D